# Feature topology & cache feed-forward
direction: down

req: Scoring request\ninstrument_id · account_id · category_code · amount · event_ts {shape: oval; style.fill: "#e0ecff"}

ondemand: On-demand (computed in-request) {
  f1: odf_log_amount
  f2: odf_is_night
  f3: odf_high_amount
  f4: odf_category_ordinal
}

hot: Hot — latest value {
  c: instrument counters\ntxn_cnt · fail_ratio · distinct_accts\nrefreshed ~30s (1h rolling) {shape: cylinder}
}

warm: Warm — point-in-time, fed forward {
  d: account daily\neffective at next-day 00:00 {shape: cylinder}
  m: account monthly\neffective at next-month 00:00 {shape: cylinder}
}

ref: Reference {
  p: account profile\nis_premium · age · region · decline_rate {shape: cylinder}
}

vec: feature vector {shape: parallelogram}
lgbm: LightGBM -> blocked? {shape: hexagon; style.fill: "#ffe0e0"}

req -> ondemand: amount, event_ts, category_code
req -> hot: instrument_id
req -> warm: account_id + event_ts
req -> ref: account_id
ondemand -> vec
hot -> vec
warm -> vec
ref -> vec
vec -> lgbm

note: |md
  **Feed forward:** a daily/monthly row becomes effective at period end, so an event
  uses the most recent **completed** period and carries it forward until the next
  scheduled backfill — point-in-time correct for both training and serving.
| {near: bottom-center; style.fill: "#fffbe0"}
